Key Advantages:
1.	Urban Mobility: Ideal for congested city environments
2.	Energy Efficiency: Significantly lower energy consumption than conventional vehicles
3.	Cost Effectiveness: Lower purchase price and operating costs
4.	Regulatory Benefits: Often qualify for special vehicle classifications with relaxed requirements
Market Dynamics
Growth Drivers:
•	Urbanization Trends: 68% of world population projected to live in urban areas by 2050
•	Emission Regulations: Stricter urban emission standards favoring lightweight EVs
•	Last-Mile Delivery Growth: E-commerce expansion driving demand for compact delivery vehicles
•	Mobility-as-a-Service: Shared mobility operators seeking cost-effective fleet options
Market Restraints:
•	Safety Perceptions: Consumer concerns about crash protection
•	Range Limitations: Especially for electric models
•	Infrastructure Challenges: Charging/parking accommodations in dense urban areas
•	Regulatory Hurdles: Varying classification standards across regions
